<doc id="326540" wikidata="Q5385318" url="?curid=326540" title="Erdős cardinal">
<text>In mathematics, an Erdős cardinal, also called a partition cardinal is a certain kind of large cardinal number introduced by .

A cardinal formula_1 is called formula_2-Erdős if for every function formula_3, there is a set of order type formula_2 that is homogeneous for formula_5. In the notation of the partition calculus, formula_1 is formula_2-Erdős if

:formula_8.

Under this definition, any cardinal larger than the least formula_2-Erdős cardinal is formula_2-Erdős.

The existence of zero sharp implies that the constructible universe formula_11 satisfies &quot;for every countable ordinal formula_2, there is an formula_2-Erdős cardinal&quot;. In fact, for every indiscernible formula_1, formula_15 satisfies &quot;for every ordinal formula_2, there is an formula_2-Erdős cardinal in formula_18&quot; (the Lévy collapse to make formula_2 countable).

However, the existence of an formula_20-Erdős cardinal implies existence of zero sharp. If formula_5 is the satisfaction relation for formula_11 (using ordinal parameters), then the existence of zero sharp is equivalent to there being an formula_20-Erdős ordinal with respect to formula_5. Thus, the existence of an formula_20-Erdős cardinal implies that the axiom of constructibility is false.

The least formula_26-Erdős cardinal is not weakly compact,p. 39. nor is the least formula_20-Erdős cardinal.p. 39

If formula_1 is formula_2-Erdős, then it is formula_2-Erdős in every transitive model satisfying &quot;formula_2 is countable.&quot;

==Dodd&#x27;s Notion of Erdős Cardinals==

For a limit ordinal formula_2, a cardinal formula_1 is less often called formula_2-Erdős if for every closed unbounded formula_35 and every function formula_36 such that formula_37 for all formula_38, there is a set formula_39 of order-type formula_2 that is homogeneous for formula_5.p. 138.

An equivalent definition is that formula_1 is formula_2-Erdős if for any formula_44, there is a set formula_45 of order-type formula_2 of order-indiscernibles for the structure formula_47 such that:

* for every formula_48, formula_49, and
* for every formula_50, the set formula_51 forms a set of order-indiscernibles for the structure formula_52.

The least cardinal formula_1 to satisfy the partition relation formula_8 is still formula_2-Erdős under this definition. Every formula_26-Erdős cardinal is an inaccessible limit of ineffable cardinals.

